"NOT FOUND"|"sarcinas : The personal baggage of the legionary. On the march he carried his own food supply, cooking utensils, blanket, and one or two rampart stakes. This luggage was done up in a bundle and suspended from a forked pole, which he carried over his shoulder. The pole was forked, like a crutch, and served much the same purpose to a weary soldier, standing at rest. Marius devised this, and hence the phrase, the *** mules of Marius.*** The entire weight of this individual luggage, or sarcinae, was often fully sixty pounds."

